<HEADLINE> 7 Rebels Killed, 3 Rebel Bases Destroyed in SriLanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan government troops
killed at least seven members of the rebel Liberation Tigers of
Tamil Eelam (LTTE) and destroyed three of their bases on Monday in
a battle in the Eastern Province, a military spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
He said that after an operation in Vakaral, the army and the
navy launched a joint operation in Batticaloa early Monday.
</P>
<P>
After blocking the possible escape routes, the government
troops searched and destroyed the rebel bases in Kokkadichoiai,
Thikodai and Santhimalai.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said the troops had approached the rebel bases
early Monday morning after a long march throughout the night.
</P>
<P>
At least seven rebels were killed and a policeman was injured,
the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the navy and the army patrolled Batticaloa lagoon
and destroyed three boats used by LTTE rebels, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE is fighting against the government for a separate
state in Sri Lanka's north and east, where more than 2 million
Tamil minority people live. 
</P>
</TEXT>
