<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1500 GMT June 29 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD -- Pakistan disclosed for the first time on Monday
that the six nuclear tests it conducted last month included one
main test, four sub-kiloton tests and one miniaturized device,
which were "totally contained and safe".
</P>
<P>
The main test was conducted on May 28 at 1516 local time in the
Raskoh range of Chagai, in the remote Balochistan province, said
an official press release received here Monday
afternoon. (Pak-Nuclear Tests)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
SHANGHAI -- U.S. President Bill Clinton arrived in Shanghai
from Beijing by presidential plane Monday evening on his third leg
of his nine-day state visit to China.
</P>
<P>
Twenty-six years ago, Chinese Premier Zhou Enlai and U.S.
President Richard Nixon signed here the Joint Communique Between
the People's Republic of China and the United States of America
which ushered in a new era in Sino-U.S. relations.
</P>
<P>
President Clinton and his wife Hillary arrived at the Shanghai
Hongqiao International Airport at about 19:15 p.m. (11:15
GMT). (China-Clinton-Shanghai-Arrival (details added)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu on
Monday tried again to squeeze the Palestinians, saying that if
they implement their commitments, a peace agreement would be
reached in the near future.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to reporters after his meeting with his Spanish
counterpart Jose Maria Aznar on Monday, Netanyahu said that "peace
is very, very close if the Palestinians do their part."
</P>
<P>
"Peace is based on reciprocity," he said, demanding the
Palestinian National Authority (PNA) must fulfill its commitments
to the security of Israel. (Israel-Palestine-Netanyahu )
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BEIJING -- General Electric (GE) Inc. of the United States
signed a contract worth 160 million U.S. dollars Monday with the
Shandong Huaneng Power Development Corp. to provide key equipment
for the Dezhou Power Plant in east China's Shandong Province.
</P>
<P>
This is another major deal between GE and China. The two sides
have signed 10 memorandums of understanding (MOU), or letters of
intent (LOI), for future cooperation in the last two months, said
Goran S. Malm, senior vice-president of GE and president of GE
Asia Pacific. (China-US-Big Deal)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ANKARA -- The death toll has risen to 116 as more bodies were
uncovered by rescue workers in southern Turkey, hit by a strong
earthquake on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
According to the latest statistics issued by the Turkish Crisis
Table Monday morning, so far more than 1,500 people have been
injured and 300 out of them have been hospitalized.
</P>
<P>
The quake, measuring 6.3 degrees on the Richter scale, struck
Adana and Ceyhan, about 400 kilometers southwest of Ankara,
capital of Turkey. (Turkey-Quake)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BEIJING -- China and the United States sealed an agreement on
cooperation concerning peaceful use of nuclear technology here
Monday.
</P>
<P>
In addition to two others, this agreement is seen here as
another important one, which will play a positive role in
bilateral cooperation in peaceful use of nuclear
technology. (China-U.S.-Nuclear-Agreement) 
</P>
