<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bierhoff Lifts Germany to 2-1 Win over Mexico </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MONTPELLIER, France, June 29 (Xinhua) -- A late winner from Oliver
Bierhoff lifted Germany to a 2-1 win over Mexico in the second round
of the soccer World Cup here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The header, which came in the 85th minute on a pass from
second-half substitute Ulf Kirsten, sent the European champions to the
quarterfinals, where they will meet the winners of Tuesday's match
between Romania and Croatia.
</P>
<P>
Luis Hernandez put Mexico 1-0 ahead by slotting the ball home past
German keeper Andreas Kopke only two minutes into the second half.
</P>
<P>
German veteran Lothar Matthaus almost scored a own goal when he
sent the ball against the left-hand post in the 61st minute in an
attempt to clear a loose ball.
</P>
<P>
Mexico's Cuauhtemoc Blanco and Hernandez tried to pounce on but
Kopke made two successive saves.
</P>
<P>
The Germans stepped up attacks and equalized in the 74th minute
through captain Jurgen Klinsmann, who scored from within the penalty
area.
</P>
<P>
In the goalless first half, Tottenham Hotspur striker Klinsmann had
an early chance in the 28th minute when his header was saved by
Mexican keeper Jorge Campos.
</P>
<P>
Bierhoff, who plays for Italian side Udinese, had two opportunities
within a span of two minutes, shotting a long-range ball into the arms
of Campos in the 38th minute and head another onto the crossbar one
minute later.
</P>
<P>
Mexico's Francisco Palencia also had chance in the 42nd minute when
he shot from within the penalty area but the ball was captured by
Andreas Kopke. 
</P>
</TEXT>
