<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bangladesh, India to Enhance Economic Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh and India decided on
Monday to strengthen cooperation in all fields, particularly in
the field of economy.
</P>
<P>
At a meeting here with his Bangladeshi counterpart Mustafizur
Rahman, visiting Indian Foreign Office Secretary K. Raghunath said
India would reduce tariff on goods from Bangladesh to help
Bangladeshi products enter the Indian market.
</P>
<P>
Raghunath arrived here Sunday on a two-day visit to Bangladesh
following a visit to India by Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina earlier
this month.
</P>
<P>
Describing the visit as a "short follow-up" of the New Delhi
meeting between the prime ministers of the two countries,
Raghunath said on Sunday that his visit gave "an opportunity to
review...and update the existing excellent relationship between
the two countries."
</P>
<P>
This was the first meeting between the foreign secretaries of
the two countries after India's Baratiya Janata Party came to
power earlier this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
