<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, June 29 (Xinhua) -- French President Jacques Chirac
left for Angola Monday afternoon, ending his 24-hour state visit
to Mozambique.
</P>
<P>
During his first visit to Mozambique, Chirac and Mozambican
President Joaquim Chissano signed four cooperative agreements
worth 10 million U.S. Dollars.
</P>
<P>
