<HEADLINE> Middle East Economic Briefs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, June 29 (Xinhua) -- The following are economic briefs
from Middle East countries.
</P>
<P>
CAIRO -- The European Union (EU) will provide 1 billion U.S.
dollars to help upgrade the Egyptian industry before it faces
European competition, the Middle East News Agency reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
The funds will be used to promote the Egyptian industry through
various ways, including conducting research and training workers,
during the first three years of the application of the Egyptian-EU
partnership agreement due to be sealed this summer.
</P>
<P>
Egypt seeks to double its exports to Europe after the signing
of the agreement which will allow Egypt to sell agro-industrial
commodities to EU markets.
</P>
<P>
CAIRO -- Egypt's economy is facing a difficult situation due to
the decline of oil prices in the world markets, the Egyptian
Al-Alam Al-Yom daily reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
Egypt lost 1 billion Egyptian pounds (294 million dollars) in
oil revenues from January to March this year compared with the
same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The Egyptian oil prices went down remarkably during the last
months, bringing down the oil revenues to less than 1.99 billion
pounds (585 million dollars) compared with 2.17 billion pounds
(638 million dollars) in the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
TEHRAN -- Iran announced on Monday that it has finished
building the fourth oil platform to be installed in the Sirri
offshore oil field in the Gulf.
</P>
<P>
Managing Director of Vali Asr industrial complex in Hormozgan
province Massood Rabbani said the 65-meter and 1,415-tonne
platform was designed and constructed by Iranian experts in four
months.
</P>
<P>
He said the platform is one of the five to be installed in the
Sirri B region.
</P>
<P>
JERICHO, WEST BANK -- Japan will provide 100 million
U.S. dollars in aid to the Palestinian National Authority (PNA) to
help it improve environment and education systems, PNA officials
announced here Monday.
</P>
<P>
Launching the first stage of the aid program, Japanese
Ambassador to Israel Yutaka Kawashima signed with PNA Minister of
Local Governments Saeb Erekat a 7.5 million dollar deal to provide
the PNA with machines and equipment for garbage disposal in the
West Bank.
</P>
<P>
Erekat said that Japan and the PNA will set up more joint
services including joint schools and water systems with the aid.
</P>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY -- Kuwait Monday signed an agreement with a French
company to buy a modern patrol vessel for its Coast Guards.
</P>
<P>
Kuwait's Interior Ministry said the boat is one of the most
sophisticated vessels and would be equipped with advanced
communication, radar and cruising instruments.
</P>
<P>
The ministry added that the purchase was part of its plan to
upgrade the skills and equipments of the Coast Guards in order to
better fight illicit trade and infiltration. 
</P>
