<HEADLINE> Iran to Boost Labor Exports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Iran Monday opened four fairs to
introduce its technical, engineering and export services with an
aim to boost labor exports, the official news agency IRNA reported.
</P>
<P>
Iranian Deputy Commerce Minister and head of the Export
Promotion Center Mojtaba Khosrowtaj told the fairs' inaugural
ceremony that the specialized fairs would help increase the
exports of Iranian work force to foreign markets.
</P>
<P>
According to official statistics, Iran earned more than 906
million U.S. dollars over the past three years from export of
technical and engineering services.
</P>
<P>
Khosrowtaj said the figure would rise to 1.3 billion
U.S. dollars if the revenues made by Iranian companies abroad are
taken into consideration.
</P>
<P>
Iran's public and private sectors are implementing 53
development and economic projects in foreign countries, according
to the official.
</P>
<P>
Some 220 private and public engineering, technical, service and
manufacturing companies attended the five-day fairs, the news
agency said.
</P>
<P>
On the sidelines of the fairs, five seminars are to be held to
study the role of insurance and export guarantee fund in boosting
export of non-oil commodities and introduce the activities of the
Central Bank of Iran and Export Promotion Bank of Iran.
</P>
<P>
The seminars are also to focus on new programs adopted by
Iran's Customs Office to ease customs procedures for non-oil
exports and the importance of free trade zone and tourism in
raising exports. 
</P>
</TEXT>
