<HEADLINE> Chirac Arrives in Angola for First State Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, June 29 (Xinhua) -- French President Jacques Chirac
arrived here Monday, starting his 48-hour visit to Angola at the
invitation of Angolan President Eduardo dos Santos.
</P>
<P>
This is the first visit of a French president to the southern
African country and it is the last leg of Chirac's trip to the
southern Africa.
</P>
<P>
The main purpose of the trip is to strengthen the economic
cooperation between the two nations
</P>
<P>
In a signed article contributed by the French president in the
daily O Jornal de Angola published Monday, Chirac said that
development cannot be achieved without stability in the region.
</P>
<P>
The French president believed that Angolan peace is relevant
to the stability in the region and there would be no stability
unless peace is achieved in the southern African country.
</P>
<P>
The full implementation of the Lusaka Peace Protocol reached
in 1994 by the two warring sides is the sole guarantee for
Angolan peace, said Chirac.
</P>
<P>
The French president said he is sure that the Lusaka peace
accord will be fully implemented and final peace will be
eventually achieved in Angola.
</P>
<P>
During the 48-hour visit, Chirac will hold talks with the
Angolan leaders and meet business leaders broadly, exchanging
views on cooperation between the two countries. And the two
countries will sign a couple of cooperative agreements.
</P>
<P>
Chirac came to Angola after visiting Namibia, South Africa and
Mozambique.
</P>
<P>
France is one of the first countries who recognized the
independence of Angola. The two countries maintain close
cooperative relations in such fields as industry, agriculture,
health, fishery, petroleum, education and culture.
</P>
<P>
Both France and Angola hope to beef up the bilateral
cooperation and broaden the fields of the cooperation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
