<HEADLINE> Romania, Croatia Similar in Style </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BORDEAUX, France, June 29 (Xinhua) -- When Romania play in Stade
Lescure here on Tuesday, they will find they are sharing many
characteristics with World Cup debutants Croatia.
</P>
<P>
Both teams are brimmed with creative players and possess techinical
prowess.
</P>
<P>
They also have strong midfields, with Gheorghe Hagi being the
playmaker for the Romanians and Zvonimir Boban on the Croatian side.
</P>
<P>
Romanian coach Anghel Iordanescu said it was hard to make a
prediction of the outcome.
</P>
<P>
"The chances are 50-50. No one's the favorite," he said. "Croatia
have a game very similiar to our own."
</P>
<P>
The Romanians, who dyed their hair gold after a bet with
Iordanescu, rested five key players in its 1-1 draw with Tunisia after
they had qualified.
</P>
<P>
The unified hair color signifies the much cherished team spirit,
which striker Viorel Moldovan said would be the best weapon.
</P>
<P>
"Our own best asset is the team spirit which has already helped
against England," said Moldovan, who plays for Coventry City in
England.
</P>
<P>
"In the match against Croatia, I believe both teams have the same
chances. We know all our opponents. All of them play in European
championships and are very skilled," he said on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Romania will depend much on Moldovan and his striking partner
Adrian Ilie from Valencia in the front.
</P>
<P>
Besides Hagi, Dorinel Munteanu is also effective in organizing
attacks by sending diagonal passes.
</P>
<P>
Defenders Gica Popescu and Dan Petrescu are dangerous when they
surge ahead to aid the attacks.
</P>
<P>
On the Croatian side, their biggest setback was the missing of
Zvonimir Soldo, who was banned after collecting two yellow cards in
the group competition.
</P>
<P>
But Croatian coach Miroslav Blazevic was confident with lessons
gained from the match against Argentina.
</P>
<P>
"We are confident about this round of sixteen match. We controlled
(Gabriel) Batistuta and (Ariel) Ortega during the match against
Argentina on Friday. I think we will manage to block the Romanians
Popescu and Moldovan in the same way," he said.
</P>
<P>
Blazevic added, "Mentally all of the players have a total will to
win and it's in that state of mind that will must go onto the pitch if
we want to win."
</P>
<P>
The biggest problem of Croatia is the age of its key players as
Boban, striker Davor Suker and midfielder Robert Prosinecki are all
veterans. 
</P>
</TEXT>
