utilization of Greek military aircraft in the south, the
Gecitkale air base will be used as a permanent military base
ready to operate at any second," the Anatolia News Agency quoted
Denktash as saying.
</P>
<P>
At present, all necessary measures are being taken to that
effect, he said.
</P>
<P>
Six Turkish F-16 fighters flew to the Gecitkale airport on
June 18 in response to the landing of four F-16 fighters and two
C-130 transport planes of the Greek Air Force at Paphos air base
on the west coast of Cyprus on June 16.
</P>
<P>
Greece and Turkey have accused each other of escalating tension
in Cyprus.
</P>
<P>
Cyprus has been divided into the Greek Cypriots-dominated south
and Turkish Cypriots-controlled north since 1974 when Turkey landed
its troops and took over the northern third of the island after a
failed coup by the Greek Cypriots seeking union with Greece.
</P>
<P>
The Turkish Cypriots declared in 1983 the breakaway "Turkish
Republic of Northern Cyprus" which is recognized only by Ankara
against the internationally recognized Republic of Cyprus.
</P>
<P>
Turkey stations more than 35,000 troops in northern Cyprus.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
