<HEADLINE> Argentina Historically Lead England </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Argentina have met England only three
times in the history of the World Cup finals and lead by two victories
against one loss.
</P>
<P>
The last meeting between the two sides was in 1986 in Mexico, where
Argentina beat England 2-1 in the quarterfinals on way to winning the
cup.
</P>
<P>
Soccer legend Diego Maradona scored both goals, including the
infamous "Hand of God" goal which Maradona deflected in with his hand.
</P>
<P>
Twenty years earlier, they also met in the quarterfinals, which was
won by England 1-0. England eventually won the 1966 World Cup by
beating Germany 4-2.
</P>
<P>
Their first meeting was during the 1962 finals in Chile, where
England beat the South American powerhouse 3-1 before being knocked
out in the quarterfinals against final winners Brazil.
</P>
<P>
Argentina will meet England in second round of the ongoing World
Cup finals in Saint-Etienne on Tuesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
