<HEADLINE> Saudi King Urges Solution to Middle East Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Saudi King Fahd Ibn Abdul-Aziz
Monday urged more efforts to solve the crisis in the Middle East
peace process, the Kuwait News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
During a speech to the Consultative Council in the Saudi
capital Riyadh, King Fahd said a solution must be found to break
the deadlock in the peace process in order to restore the full
legitimate rights of the Palestinian people. He renewed his
support to the establishment of an independent Palestinian state.
