<HEADLINE> UNAIDS Strives to Help Developing Countries Bridge Care Gap </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, June 30 (Xinhua) -- The first shipments of AIDS drugs
since the launch of the UNAIDS Drug Access Initiative in late 1997
have arrived in Cote d'Ivoire and Uganda, the two countries'
health ministers announced here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Ugandan Health Minister C. Kiyonga and Cote d'Ivoirean Health
Minister Maurice Kacou Guikahue, who are attending the 12th World
