continue improving health services. Maurice Kacou Guikahue said
that his government had decided to allocate one million
U.S. dollars as a start-up to a solidarity fund that would help
extend access to care. Ways of ensuring the sustainability of this
fund were being explored.
</P>
<P>
The two African countries and Chile and Vietnam are the four
participating in the initial pilot phase of the UNAIDS
initiative. 
