<HEADLINE> Hoddle: "Hand of God" not Maradona's Fault </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SAINT-ETIENNE, June 30 (Xinhua) -- The infamous "Hand of God" goal
in the 1986 World Cup finals was not Diego Maradona's fault, according
to England coach Glenn Hoddle.
</P>
<P>
"The 'hand of God' wasn't Maradona's fault, nor Argentina's fault,
but the referee's," said Hoddle, whose team will meet the South
Americans in the second round here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
In the quarterfinals in 1986, Maradona deflected the ball into the
net with his hand but the referee failed to spot it.
</P>
<P>
"The match against Argentina won't be a revenge of the
quarterfinals in 1986, we just want to qualify," said Hoddle, who
himself was in the squad 12 years ago.
</P>
<P>
Hoddle said the present team was better than that of 1986, even
though they sometimes showed the lack of experience.
</P>
<P>
"In four years time, the young players will develop their
potential," said Hoddle. 
</P>
