<HEADLINE> Rainstorms Blamed for Deaths, Damage in Sichuan Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Rainstorms Monday in Sichuan
Province, one of the most populated areas of China, have been
blamed for a total of at least 13 deaths and heavy economic losses.
</P>
<P>
A landslide in Zigong, a city in the southern part of the
province, caused by the torrential rain halted highway
transportation and caused 11 deaths and four injuries, according
to local officials.
</P>
