In addition, 1,729 persons were still missing in Kutch district
and 128 in Rajkot following the cyclone, which had pounded a total
of 2,938 villages in the State.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, heavy rains lashed several parts of the state in the
last 24 hours with Datha-Banaskantha district recording the
highest rainfall of 118 mm. 
</P>
</TEXT>
