<HEADLINE> Jiangsu Marks 1st Anniversary of Hong Kong's Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Some 40 representatives of
different sectors today gathered in the Jinghai Temple in Nanjing,
capital of east China's Jiangsu Province, to celebrate the first
anniversary of the return of Hong Kong to the motherland.
</P>
<P>
The temple, where the Treaty of Nanking was signed ceding Hong
Kong to Britain, became a base for patriotic education in China.
</P>
<P>
The economic, trade and cultural cooperation between Jiangsu
and Hong Kong was further reinforced in 1997 based on their
comprehensive exchanges in the fields of politics, business,
journalism and public affairs, said Gu Hao, Deputy Secretary of
the Jiangsu Provincial Committee of the Communist Party of China
(CPC).
</P>
<P>
Official statistics show that the export volume to Hong Kong of
Jiangsu has reached 19.6 billion U.S. dollars since 1974, with an
annual increase of 25.89 percent.
</P>
<P>
The number of enterprises set up by Hong Kong businessmen in
the province has reached 15,000, according to Gu. 
</P>
