<HEADLINE> Editorial to Mark 77th Birth Anniversary of CPC </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 30 (Xinhua) -- The People's Daily will
publish an editorial tomorrow to mark the 77th anniversary of the
founding of the Communist Party of China (CPC) and extend
festival greetings to CPC members of different circles.
</P>
<P>
The editorial, entitled "Unify Our Thinking And Concentrate Our
Efforts", says that as China's state enterprise reform, financial
reform and government institutional reform are all entering a
critical period, the leadership of the CPC has become more
important.
</P>
<P>
It says that a notice, to be issued Wednesday by the CPC
Central Committee on the study of Deng Xiaoping Theory, will
elaborate on the importance and urgency of the study of the theory.
</P>
<P>
The notice, which establishes new requirements for research and
study on the theory, insists that CPC members, especially those
who are senior government officials, should have a thorough
and deep understanding of the theory.
</P>
<P>
The editorial stresses that all CPC members should manage to
reach a common understanding of the present domestic and
international circumstances and, under the correct guidance of the
CPC Central Committee, work whole-heartedly to overcome
difficulties ahead.
</P>
<P>
The pivotal role of the Party and the concerted efforts of the
nation are of significant importance to the final success,
the editorials emphasizes.
</P>
<P>
More than 70 years of revolutionary struggles have helped the
Party to come to the conclusion that a great and promising Party
should be able to mobilize the people and unite with all forces
that can be united.
</P>
<P>
The editorial says that CPC members should be aware of their
historical responsibilities, never neglect the rights and
interests of the masses, and dedicate themselves whole-heartedly
to the great cause of communism.
</P>
<P>
The editorial calls on all CPC members to rally around the CPC
Central Committee, with Jiang Zemin as the core, and hold high the
great banner of Deng Xiaoping Theory to unite China's 1.2
billion people to meet new challenges and achieve new
successes. 
</P>
