<HEADLINE> Sino-Portuguese JLG Starts 32nd Plenary Session </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, June 30 (Xinhua) -- The Sino-Portuguese Joint Liaison
Group (JLG) started its 32nd plenary session here on Tuesday, to
discuss the localization of civil servants and other major
transitional issues in Macao.
</P>
<P>
On the first day of the three-day meeting, the two sides
discussed the three leading issues -- localization of civil
servants, the localization and translation of law and the use of
Chinese language as an official language, said Han Zhaokang, chief
representative of the Chinese side, in a briefing after a
five-hour meeting.
</P>
<P>
The two sides also exchanged views on the official status of
Portuguese language, he said.
</P>
<P>
While giving a positive assessment on the progress on the three
leading issues, Han urged the Portuguese side to take concrete
measures to step up the localization of chief of government
departments in Macao and to implement the official status of
Chinese language in Macao's administration, legislature and
judiciary organs.
</P>
<P>
In addition, he said the localization of the major laws in
Macao should be completed within 1998 as time is limited now.
</P>
<P>
In return, Portuguese chief representative Antonio Carlos said
that Macao Government has made great efforts in the localization
of civil servants, and his side will make utmost efforts with the
Chinese side to finish the localization of law before the end of
the transitional period.
</P>
<P>
The JLG holds three plenary sessions each year in Macao,
Beijing and Lisbon respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
