<HEADLINE> Fastest Inland River Ship Built in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai Qiuxin Shipyard has
completed construction of an inland-river vessel with a speed of
80 kilometers per hour, the fastest of its kind in China.
</P>
<P>
"Yuanzhou-1," the vessel, is 29 meters long, 7.2 meters
wide, and 6.9 meters high with a passenger capacity of 108.
</P>
<P>
This is a new type of vessel built to cater to the increasing
demand of high-speed water transport in the country, according to
a source from the China State Shipbuilding Corp. (CSSC).
</P>
<P>
The vessel was designed and built by Shenzhen Yuanzhou Science
and Technology Industrial Development Corp., with a direct
investment of 9 million yuan. Work on the vessel started in
November of 1996.
</P>
<P>
Another source said the vessel will be put into use on the
shipping route from Wanxian to Chongqing on the upper Yangtze
River and the route will be extended to Yichang.
</P>
<P>
More than 200 high-speed vessels run on more than 70 routes in
China, according to the CSSC.  
</P>
</TEXT>
