<HEADLINE> HK Airport Relocation Will Continue as Scheduled </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 30 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Airport Authority
(HKAA) confirmed here Today that the new airport relocation
exercise will continue as scheduled.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong Observatory has at this point forecast no adverse
weather condition that would affect airport relocation movements,
the HKAA said in a "situation report on airport relocation" sent
to airlines, business partners and the media.
</P>
<P>
"The new airport at Chek Lap Kok remains on schedule to be in
operation and receive the first arriving flight at 06:30 hours on
Monday, July 6, 1998," the HKAA said.
</P>
<P>
Business concerns involved in tourism, travel and hotel
industries are requested to take note of the position and inform
their customers accordingly.
</P>
<P>
A further report will be issued on July 3.
</P>
<P>
The unprecedented relocation comprises of five phases over a
three-month period, of which the night move during the late hours
of July 5 and the early hours of July 6 is most critical. 
