<HEADLINE> River Dike Breached in Guangdong Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, June 30 (Xinhua) -- A dike was breached on a
tributary of the Beijiang River in south China's Guangdong
Province early today. No casualties have been reported so far.
</P>
<P>
The width of the breach, located at Danzao Town, has reached
80-to-90 meters, causing the water flow to hit 1,000 cubic meters
per second.
</P>
<P>
Floods affected an area of 23,000 hectares and a population of
320,000, local sources said.
</P>
<P>
The local population had been dispersed because of timely
predictions of the disaster and well-done preparations, the
sources said.
</P>
<P>
Li Changchun, member of the Political Bureau of the Communist
Party of China (CPC) Central Committee and Secretary of the
Guangdong Provincial Committee of the CPC, and some other local
Party and government officials have rushed to the site to conduct
disaster relief work. 
</P>
</TEXT>
