<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Stocks Close Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks rose 0.97
percent in the pre-holiday trade on Tuesday on easing interbank
rates and firmer Japanese yen.
</P>
<P>
The local stock market will be closed for one day on Wednesday,
a public holiday.
</P>
<P>
The key Hang Seng Index gained 82.39 points to close at
8,543.10 on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The index gained 86.71 points, or 1.02 percent, to open at
8,547.41 Tuesday morning. It rose 120.47 points, or 1.42 percent,
to close at 8,581.18 midday.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover decreased by 1,748 million HK dollars (224
million U.S. dollars) to register at 4,470 million HK dollars (573
million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong stock prices dropped 147.15 points, or 1.71 percent,
to close at 8,460.71 on Monday. 
</P>
