<HEADLINE> Japan to Reveal Financial Reform Plan: Clinton </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 30 (Xinhua) -- "The Japanese government is going
to disclose in the next couple of days what it intends to do in
the area of financial reform," visiting President Bill Clinton
said here today.
</P>
<P>
Clinton revealed this at a live radio call-in show here
today when asked what should be done to cope with the current
Southeast Asian economic crisis.
</P>
<P>
"We cannot see growth in Asia unless it is restored in Japan,"
he said, adding that now, in Japan the people are about to have an
election for the upper house of the Diet, "this is not an easy
time for them," but the government is going to make public of its
financial reform plans soon. 
</P>
