<HEADLINE> New Map Shows Australia 5 Million Years ago </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, June 30 (Xinhua) -- A new map, a result of 30 years
of study into Antarctic rocks by Australian and Russian experts,
has been produced, giving a glimpse into how Australia was formed
500 million years ago, Australian Resources and Energy Minister
Warwick Parer said here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
"The Australian Geological Survey Organization has produced a
special map based on 30 years of research by Russian and
Australian scientists... providing a window into the formation of
Gondwana," Parer said at the launch of the map.
</P>
<P>
Gondwana was the name for the world land mass that originally
linked Australia to Asia and Antarctica.
</P>
<P>
"Special focus of attention for the Russian and Australian
scientists has been the world's largest glacier, the Lambert
Glacier in Prydz Bay in the Antarctic," Parer said.
</P>
<P>
"The rocks exposed in the Prince Charles Mountains along its
side provide a window into the formation of Gondwana 500 million
years ago, and the early history of the Earth 3.2 billion years
ago."
</P>
<P>
The map encapsulated Russian geology and geophysics as well as
Australian results, and is able to be updated regularly, the
minister said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
