<HEADLINE> Singapore Stock Market Loses Ground </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, June 30 (Xinhua) -- The Singapore Stock Market lost
ground Tuesday despite the government announced Monday a package
of off-budget measures to bolster the economy.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Industrials Index (STII) lost 18.49
points to close at 1,066.66 points.
</P>
<P>
The total volume was 122.19 million shares, valued at 251.40
million Singapore dollars (about 148.76 million U.S. dollars).
Losers led gainers by 154 to 95 with 339 stocks remained
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
The most active stock was SingTel which had 10.28 million
shares traded. It was followed by Easyknit thk which had 7.37
million units traded. DBS Land was next with 6.38 million shares
changing hands.
</P>
<P>
NatBroad topped gainers of the day as it rose by 35 cents to
close at 1.00 U.S. dollar. RothmansI was 25 cents up to close at
7.50 Singapore dollars. CityDev gained 24 cents to end at 4.72
Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Venture w99 was the biggest lower as it shed
80 cents to finish at 2.10 Singapore dollars. SPH was 70 cents
down to end at 11.30 Singapore dollars. Venture was next as it
fell by 36 cents to close at 3.20 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said the fall indicated that the much anticipated
off-budget measures failed to lift market sentiment.
</P>
<P>
Analysts said although the package provided measures to reduce
corporate costs and control supply in the property market, it
failed to offer much to spur demand. 
</P>
</TEXT>
