<HEADLINE> Maldives President to Visit Pakistan Wednesday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 30 (Xinhua) -- President Maumoon Abdul Gayoom
of the Maldives is paying an official visit to Pakistan on July
1-2 in his capacity as Chairman of the South Asian Association for
Regional Cooperation (SAARC), said an official press release
issued on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
During his two-day visit, Qayoom will hold formal talks with
Pakistani Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif and President Rafiq Tarar,
the release said.
</P>
<P>
Official talks between Qayoom and Sharif will cover matters
relating to regional cooperation under SAARC as well as the whole
gamut of Pakistan-Maldives bilateral relations, it said.
</P>
<P>
The two sides will consider ways and means to consolidate and
further expand relations between the two countries, it added.
</P>
<P>
Gayoom's visit to Pakistan is in keeping with SAARC tradition,
whereby a head of state or government before the end of his tenure
as chairman undertakes visits to SAARC member states to apprise
them of the activities of the association under his chairmanship.
He has so far visited Bangladesh, Bhutan, Nepal, Sri Lanka and
India. 
