<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Seven people were killed in
two separate road accidents in South Africa's eastern province of
Kwazulu-Natal, South African Press Association reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Six people abroad a light delivery vehicle were killed when
the vehicle collided head-on with a truck Saturday night outside
Eshowe, a town 30 kilometers from the Indian coast.
</P>
<P>
Six occupants of the vehicle, including the driver, died
instantly while three others were seriously injured, a traffic
spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
He said the driver of the light delivery vehicle lost control
before it hit the oncoming truck.
</P>
<P>
In another accident Monday morning, a driver of a light
delivery vehicle was killed and four people injured when the
vehicle crashed into a barrier on the N2 national highway outside
Durban, an Indian seaport.
</P>
<P>
One of the victims was seriously injured, the spokesman said.
He said causes of the two incidents would be investigated.
