halls or rooms, the principal hall having 2,500 seats. There are
multi-language simultaneous interpretation devices at every seat.
</P>
<P>
Arjun K. Damai, president of Sewa, said at the signing ceremony
that economic cooperation has become a key component for China and
U.S. to supplement each other, noting he feels much confident of
investing in Guilin.
</P>
<P>
Li Jinzao, executive vice-mayor of Guilin and director of the
high-tech zone, said today that he is optimistic about the
project, expecting more domestic and overseas investors in Guilin.
</P>
<P>
With high working efficiency, preferential investment policies
and good infrastructure, the zone has attracted more than 70
investor enterprises from other countries including the U.S.,
Britain, France, Japan and Australia as well as from the regions
of Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
So far, the zone has more than 900 enterprises engaged in
electronic information, electronically controlled machinery,
biological medicine, new materials and environmental protection.
