<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 60 S. Leonean Rebels Die in Canoe Mishap </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, June 30 (Xinhua) -- About 60 supporters of Sierra
Leone's ousted junta, including rebels of the Revolutionary
United Front (RUF), drowned at the weekend in a canoe mishap in
the east of the country, a report reaching here said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The accident took place Saturday when canoes crossing the Moa
River in the Kailahun district struck rocks and capsized, the
report said, quoting a Catholic relief organization.
</P>
<P>
It is thought the junta supporters were trying to line up with
comrades.
</P>
<P>
Last week, fishermen pulled five bodies from the Moa River,
which were also identified as rebels.
</P>
<P>
The junta, which seized power after overthrowing the elected
civilian government in a coup in May last year, was ousted by the
west African peace-keeping force known as ECOMOG this February.
</P>
<P>
The remnants of the junta, as well as those of its allied RUF
rebels, escaped for guerrilla war in the north and east of the
country.
</P>
<P>
ECOMOG is stepping up its efforts in a mopping up exercise in
order to wipe them out completely in an early date. 
</P>
