<HEADLINE> Forest Parks Set up for Historical Chinese City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Xi'an, June 30 (Xinhua) -- The city of Xi'an, the capital of
northwest China's Shaanxi Province, has set up 10 forest parks
that are open to the public.
</P>
<P>
The parks were developed along the Qinling Mountain ranges on
some 65,000 hectares of land and have 1,670 sightseeing spots,
most of them capitalizing on natural sites.
</P>
<P>
The largest park is Louguantai Forest Park, which occupies
33,658 hectares, and the smallest is Lishan, which occupies 73
hectares.
</P>
<P>
Last year the parks had received more than 800,000 tourists and
earned 13 million yuan (1.57 million US dollars) in income from
tourism.  
