<HEADLINE> France to Strengthen Ties with Angola: Chirac </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Visiting French President Jacques
Chirac has said that the aim of his current visit is to
strengthen bilateral ties so as to expand their future
cooperations.
</P>
<P>
Chirac made the remarks here on Monday night at a banquet
hosted by Angolan President Eduardo dos Santos in his honor.
</P>
<P>
France and Angola have been enjoying friendly cooperative
relations in the traditional sphere, he said, adding cooperation
in areas such as economic development in the rural regions and
personnel training should be further broadened so that Angola
could play its due role in the world economy.
</P>
<P>
According to Chirac, France has rich experience in
Agriculture, animal husbandry, fishery, industry and trade, and
wishes to exchange these experiences with Angola to promote
bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
Dos Santos said in his speech that France has forged fruitful
relations with Angola in the past two decades regardless the
warring state in the southern African country, providing precious
aids especially in the energy sector.
</P>
<P>
He hoped that France will continue in its help to Angola to
ensure the success of its efforts in national security, economic
stability and exploration of resources.
</P>
<P>
Angola has benefited a lot from its collaboration with
France's Elf Aquitaine and Total oil companies, said dos Santos,
adding that he believed the two countries will establish an
economic partnership of real equality on this basis.
</P>
<P>
Chirac arrived in the Angolan capital on Monday for a two-day
visit at the invitation of dos Santos. This is the first visit
ever by a French president. During the visit, the two countries
will sign a number of cooperation agreements. 
</P>
</TEXT>
