<HEADLINE> Laser Operation Helps Hirsute Chinese Girl </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 30 (Xinhua) -- A 17-year-old Chinese girl with
excess body hair had the hair on many parts of her face removed
Wednesday by Shanghai doctors who used a U.S. laser device in the
first hair-removal operation of its kind in China.
</P>
<P>
The girl, Liu Hua, who is from China's Liaoning Province in the
Northeast, could hardly believe her eyes when she touched her
smooth face after the operation and said, "My beautiful dream has
finally come true after more than a dozen years."
</P>
<P>
This was the second operation for her. It was done by doctors
at the Shanghai No.2 Medical Science University's No.9 Hospital.
</P>
<P>
The first operation was for removing hair on lower part of her
face and she will return to Shanghai for her final treatment in
two months' time.
</P>
<P>
The laser method usually requires three or four treatments to
totally destroy the hair follicles to keep the hair from ever
reappearing.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
