<DOCNO> XIE19980630.0205 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Remains World's Largest Potential Market (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
By Wang Yuncai, Yan Wenbin
</P>
<P>
China has so far drawn more than 100 billion U.S. dollars worth
of investment from overseas and has opened its light industry,
textiles, machine-building, electronics, raw materials, and food
and hotel businesses to overseas investors, and banking,
insurance, retail sales, and foreign trade are opening on a trial
basis.
</P>
<P>
Many signs point to consumer demand in urban areas shifting
from the color TV sets and refrigerators of the past to apartments,
telephones, automobiles, computers, and education and tourism.
</P>
<P>
Domestic tourists now make up over 90 percent of China's
tourists and contribute two-thirds of the country's tourism
earnings. Mobile phone sales have been going up 120 percent and
cordless phones will soon be more common than standard telephones.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, rural areas have the most market potential, analysts
say. Statistics show Chinese farmers' per-capita annual incomes
averages at least 2,100 yuan and retail sales of consumer goods in
rural areas reaches more than a trillion yuan, with sales of farm
machinery coming in first in the machine-building sector.
</P>
<P>
According to a State Development Planning Commission official,
China has made opening up the rural market an important component
part of increased economic growth.
</P>
<P>
The state recently announced plans to concentrate investment in
infrastructure in rural areas, including some 5 billion yuan for
power grids.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, some observers hold that China's rural market will
have great energy and will become a strong force behind a new
round of economic growth, with an improved standards of living for
farmers.
</P>
<P>
China will not only become the earth's biggest investment
market, but the largest farm machinery, home appliance, insurance
policy, automobile, telecommunications, and tourism market,
offering the world unprecedented business opportunities.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980630.0206 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-30 </DATE_TIME>
