<HEADLINE> Heavy Rainstorms Hit Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 30 (Xinhua) -- The heaviest rainstorms so far
this summer hit the Chinese capital yesterday evening and lasted
until this morning, causing traffic snarls and difficulties for
people.
</P>
<P>
A Beijing Traffic Management Bureau official said that the
rainfall caused many automobiles to stall, causing serious traffic
jams in the downtown area and on the second and third ring roads
and slowed the movement of traffic.
</P>
<P>
The rain started at 10:00 yesterday evening, according to
Beijing meteorologists, and was heavier in the southeastern parts
of the city, with more than 200 millimeters in the Tongzhou
District and more than 50 millimeters in some other places.
</P>
<P>
Xu Guanzhong, the director of the Chongwen District Housing and
Land Management Bureau, told Xinhua that his bureau has to repair
520 single-storey houses and 81 multi-storey buildings in the
district because of leaks during the heavy rain.
</P>
<P>
The rain eased off by 1:00 this afternoon, and traffic in urban
areas returned to normal.
</P>
<P>
According to the Municipal Meteorology Station, there will be
thunderstorms in the Beijing area later this afternoon and into
the evening.  
</P>
</TEXT>
