<HEADLINE> Bright Prospects Ahead for Hong Kong: Newspaper </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 30 (Xinhua) -- "It is generally believed that
Hong Kong has even brighter prospects," commented the
Chinese-language newspaper Wen Wei Po here Tuesday while reporting
on worldwide reaction over the first anniversary of Hong Kong's
return to China.
</P>
<P>
"The British press has come to re-understand China and Hong
Kong," wrote the newspaper's London-based reporter.
</P>
<P>
Great changes had taken place in the coverage of Hong Kong's
pre-handover and current situation, the report said. "The smooth
transition of Hong Kong greatly changed the attitude towards China
of the British public and press," the report said.
</P>
<P>
"Hong Kong's post-handover performance has proved not only that
Hong Kong is nothing of a 'tragedy' but also that the
unprecedented concept of 'one country, two systems' is a success.
It has proved that two different systems can not only co-exist in
one country, but can also help and benefit each other," it said.
</P>
<P>
Another report from Washington said, "Noted American persons
think that Hong Kong can be the first to ride out of the regional
economic turmoil."
</P>
<P>
It said that Chinese President Jiang Zemin's visit to the Hong
Kong Special Administration Region (SAR) and participation in the
celebrations of the first anniversary of the handover is one of
the two major events in early July, which will attract worldwide
attention.
</P>
<P>
And U.S. President Bill Clinton's visit to Hong Kong, the first
ever such visit by a U.S. president, shows Americans' concern over
Hong Kong's continued smooth transition and the Chinese
government's promise of a high level of autonomy for the Hong Kong
SAR, the report quoted a former U.S. deputy secretary of state as
saying.
</P>
<P>
Many American notables are satisfactory over Hong Kong's
performance since the handover, it noted. Politically speaking,
they think, Hong Kong's handover should be taken as being very
smooth and successful.
</P>
<P>
Although Hong Kong is suffering from regional economic
downturn, its economic format remains the most open and free in
the world. With a solid financial mechanism and economic
foundation, the rule of law and a corruption-free government, Hong
Kong enjoys bright prospects, the report further said.
</P>
<P>
Southeast Asia is also one of the areas which have the closest
economic ties with Hong Kong, Wen Wei Po's Jakarta-based reporter
said. Although suffering seriously from the regional economic
crisis, Indonesians interviewed by the reporter all felt happy
with post-handover Hong Kong's achievements and they are confident
of Hong Kong's future.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong remains Southeast Asian countries' most important
partner for cooperation in the fields of social culture, finance
and investment, science, technology and information as well as
economic relations and trade, the reporter said.
</P>
<P>
Many convincing facts in the past year have approved that Hong
Kong will continue to play an important role in the process of
economic globalization and governments of many Southeast Asian
countries expressed their desire to develop even closer
cooperation with Hong Kong in various fields, the reporter added.
</P>
