</P>
<P>
YANGON -- Myanmar's private economy achieved sustainable
development in the 1997-98 fiscal year ending March,
contributing 75.4 percent to the country's gross domestic product
(GDP), according to the latest official statistics.
</P>
<P>
In the three main goods sectors which contributed the most to
the GDP in the year, the private enterprises shared 97.6 percent
in its output value in agriculture, 98.2 percent in meat and fish
and 72.2 percent in manufacturing, said a current report on the
country's financial, economic and social conditions.
(Myanmar-Economy)
</P>
