<HEADLINE> South West Monsoon Wreaks Havoc in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, June 30 (Xinhua) -- The current weather conditions
caused by an active southwest monsoon has wreaked havoc in Sri
Lanka, according to Meteorological Department sources here
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The sources said the southwest monsoonal winds have been
blowing directly across Sri Lanka from the southern hemisphere and
the winds are of an active nature estimated to be traveling at
about 100 kilometers per hour.
</P>
<P>
The stormy weather conditions have wreaked havoc in the capital
city Colombo as well as in the coastal areas. Scores of houses
were damaged. So far about 250 houses have been damaged in
Colombo, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
The Sri Lankan government is currently assessing the extent of
damage and will soon allocate funds for the payment of
compensation to those affected.
</P>
<P>
A sum of 10,000 rupees (more than 150 U.S. dollars) will be
allocated to repair each damaged house. Additionally dry rations
and cooked meals are being supplied to those affected.
</P>
<P>
The weather bureau forecasts that the weather pattern will
continue for a few more days with the rains expected to spread to
other areas as well, the sources added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
