<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading Indian Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 30 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news
items in leading Indian newspapers Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Hindustan Times:
</P>
<P>
-- The Indian cabinet Monday approved a proposal to grant full
statehood to New Delhi.
</P>
<P>
The Times of India:
</P>
<P>
-- In a bid to increase the inflow of foreign direct
investment, the government is contemplating throwing open the
agricultural sector for such investments.
</P>
<P>
