<HEADLINE> Otto Pfister Named as Coach of Saudi National Team </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT, June 29 (Xinhua) -- The Saudi Soccer Federation
announced Monday that German Otto Pfister has been named to head
the Saudi national soccer team, replacing Brazilian Carlo Albertto
Parreira, according to reports from Riyadh.
</P>
<P>
The official SPA news agency quoted the federation as saying in
a statement in Riyadh that Pfister would be assisted by Saudi
Mohammad Al-Khura.
</P>
<P>
55-year-old Parreira was let go on June 20 following the team's
1-0 defeat by Denmark and 4-0 by France in the first round of the
World Cup Finals.
</P>
<P>
Parreira led the Kuwaiti team in 1982 and the United Arab
Emirates team in 1990. 
</P>
</TEXT>
