<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Circular Calls for Study of Deng Xiaoping Theory </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 30 (Xinhua) -- The Central Committee of the
Communist Party of China (CPC) issued a circular today calling for
further study of Deng Xiaoping theory by all Party members.
</P>
<P>
The circular emphasized that further study of Deng Xiaoping
Theory is an important and urgent task which will lift the Party's
theoretical study to a higher level.
</P>
<P>
Party leaders at all levels should take the lead in the drive,
the circular stated, adding that the study will strengthen
research and publicity on the theory.
</P>
<P>
The circular urges all Party members to improve their style of
study, which it calls a political problem of great importance.
Leadership on theoretical study should be strengthened, it states.
</P>
<P>
China is in a crucial stage of development, which provides both
opportunities and challenges, according to the circular, which
stresses that the guidance of Deng Xiaoping Theory offers the
strongest support for China to overcome various difficulties it
faces.
</P>
<P>
Party education centering on theoretical study and political
awareness will be strengthened among leading officials at and
above county levels in the next two years, and an examination
system will be established to test cadres' theoretical level,
according to the circular. Test results will be used as an
important indicator in their evaluations.
</P>
<P>
The study of Deng Xiaoping Theory is of vital importance for
the Party and the country's whole development; for the lasting
development of the Chinese socialist cause; and for the future of
the Chinese nation, the circular stressed, calling on all Party
members to strengthen the study of Deng Xiaoping Theory both
self-consciously and urgently. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
