<HEADLINE> Japan to Provide Kazakhstan with Loan to Renovate Airport </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALMA ATA, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Japan has decided to give
Kazakhstan a loan worth 160 million U.S. dollars to help the
former Soviet country renovate the international airport in
Astana, the country's new capital.
</P>
<P>
Kazakh Foreign Minister Dasymzhomart Tokayev and Japanese
Ambassador to Kazakhstan Xidaikata Mitsuhashi Monday signed the
exchange of notes on the loan, which will be paid back in 30 years
with a 10-year grace period.
</P>
<P>
In 1995, Japan provided loans to Kazakhstan to help the country
rebuild the Druzhba railway port. 
