<HEADLINE> Eight Arrested on Mafia-Related Charges in Italy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Italian police Monday arrested eight
people in Ribera, a town near the southern Sicilian port of
Agrigento, in an anti-Mafia sweep against the Capizzi Mafia family.
</P>
<P>
Taken into custody were Ribera Mayor Giuseppe Di Salvo, three
sons of the alleged local Mafia boss, Simone Capizzi, and other
suspects, the ANSA news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The mayor and the town's police chief were charged in
connection with their alleged failure act on information arriving
from the Agrigento prefecture and police headquarters on the
presumed Mafia activities of the Capizzi family, the news agency
said.
</P>
<P>
All the others were charged with Mafia criminal association, it
reported.
</P>
<P>
Under focus was the transformation of a building in the center
of Ribera into a wholesale market for agricultural products.
</P>
<P>
Named in warrants signed by the magistrate in charge of the
preliminary investigation, Florestano Cristodamo, on the request
of investigating magistrate Giovanni Di Leo, were Simone Capizzi,
54, already jailed in Caltanizzetta, his 58-year-old brother,
three of the suspected Mafia boss's sons and another suspect.
</P>
</TEXT>
