<HEADLINE> Davenport, Seles Cruise into Wimbledon Quarter-final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Second seed Lindsay Davenport of
the United States cruised into the women's singles quarter-final
stage of the Wimbledon tennis championships after beating her
Spanish opponent Magu Serna 6-1, 6-0.
</P>
<P>
In another fourth-round clash, another American tennis star
Monica Seles, who ranked 6th in the tournament, also booked her
quarter-final place after trouncing the 14th-seeded Sandrine
Testud of France by 6-3, 6-2.
</P>
<P>
In some delayed third round matches, Third seed Jana Novotna of
the Czech Republic, French Open champion Arantxa Sanchez Vicario
of Spain and American Venus Willimas all entered the fourth round.
</P>
<P>
In the men's fourth round competitions, U.S. Open Champion Pat
Rafter of Australia failed to qualify for the quarter-final after
losing to 12th seed British player Tim Henman 6-3, 6-7 (3-7),6-3,
6-2.
</P>
<P>
However, third seed Petr Korda of the Czech Republic carried on
his winning streak by beating John Va Lottum of the Netherlands in
straight sets 6-3, 6-4, 7-6 (7-4).
</P>
<P>
In the men's third round matches, Defending champion American
Pete Sampras and 1996 Wimbledon champion Richard Krakicek of the
Netherlands and Croatian tennis verteran Goran Ivanisevic overcame
another hurdle after defeating their opponents. 
</P>
