<DOCNO> XIE19980630.0309 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> COMESA to Scrap Travel Visa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, June 29 (Xinhua) -- Member countries of the Common
Market for Eastern and Southern Africa (COMESA) will scrap travel
visa by the year 2000 to promote trade within the member
countries.
</P>
<P>
This was decided by the COMESA member countries at the third
COMESA Summit in Kinshasa, capital of the Democratic Republic of
Congo.
</P>
<P>
"With the complete abolition of restrictions to the internal
movements of goods under the COMESA free trade area by the year
2000, there would be greater need for business persons to move
freely within COMESA," a report from the COMESA Council of
Ministers said.
</P>
<P>
The report said that the scrapping of travel visa will also
accelerate the process of integration by removing any barriers to
the free movement of goods and factors of production.
</P>
<P>
COMESA has also agreed to mobilize about 300 million U.S.
Dollars to build its telecommunications interconnectivity
network. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
